Before picking up where we left off, quick review of chapter 5 verses 1-12 that we covered last week

Jesus opens his sermon on the mount with the beatitudes

He lays out kingdom values and outlines the character of those whom God favours, or blesses

Poor in Spirit: Reliance on God.

Those Who Mourn: Comfort for those grieving sin

The Meek: Inheriting the earth through gentleness

Hunger for Righteousness: Seeking divine justice

The Merciful: Receiving mercy by showing it

Pure in Heart: Seeing God through spiritual purity

The Peacemakers: Being recognized as children of God

The Persecuted: Receiving the kingdom for staying faithful





